TY  - JOUR
AU  - Mitton, Todd
T1  - Economic Significance in Corporate Finance
PY  - 2024
Y1  - 2024/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rcfs/cfac008
JO  - The Review of Corporate Finance Studies
JA  - Review of Corporate Finance Studies
VL  - 13
IS  - 1
SP  - 38
EP  - 79
SN  - 2046-9128
AB  - Reporting the economic significance of findings in corporate finance has become increasingly common, but a review of the literature reveals shortcomings in typical reporting practices. Researchers can more effectively communicate the practical importance of findings by using standard measures of economic significance scaled by the standard deviation of the dependent variable, by providing all statistics necessary to calculate economic significance, and by providing benchmarks by which to evaluate the magnitude of economic significance. To support these objectives, I show why measures scaled by the standard deviation are preferable, and I provide benchmarks based on hundreds of established findings from the literature. (JEL C18, C52, G30).
Y2  - 4/24/2026
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rcfs/cfac008
ER  - 




